      • getDebugModeRequestPath

        public String getDebugModeRequestPath()
        Description copied from interface: ResourceGenerator
        Returns the request path to use when generating a URL to this generator. Normally it's OK to return either ResourceGenerator.JAVASCRIPT_DEBUGPATH, ResourceGenerator.CSS_DEBUGPATH, or ResourceGenerator.IMG_DEBUGPATH but this can be modified to suit an application's path needs. Note that any prefix specified in the servlet mapping does not need to be included in the returned value.
        Specified by:
        getDebugModeRequestPath in interface ResourceGenerator
        Returns:
        the request path to use in debug mode

      • isHandlingCssImage

        public boolean isHandlingCssImage()
        Description copied from interface: CssResourceGenerator
        Returns true if the CSS image defined in the generated CSS resource are using the CSS generator. If myGen is the prefix of the resource generator, all CSS image which are defined in the CSS resources, will be prefixed by myGen. For example: if CSS image is referenced as background-image : url('/myImg/temp/myIcon.png') The image path will be interpreted as : background-image : url('myGen:/myImg/temp/myIcon.png')
        Specified by:
        isHandlingCssImage in interface CssResourceGenerator
        Returns:
        true if the CSS image defined in the generated CSS resource are using the CSS generator.
